llcaps"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:Infobox/styles.css"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:References"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:S"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:CH"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:LR"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:Gondolin"}, {"ns": 828, "exists": "", "*": "Module:Paramvalidate"}, {"ns": 828, "exists": "", "*": "Module:Arguments"}], "images": ["Jef_Murray_-_Thorondor's_Realm.jpg"], "wikitext": {"*": "{{location infobox\n| name=Crissaegrim\n| image=Jef Murray - Thorondor's Realm.jpg\n| caption=\"Thorondor's Realm\" by [[Jef Murray]]\n| pronun={{respell|kris|seye|grim}}\n| othernames=\n| location=Southern part of [[Echoriad]], south of [[Gondolin]] and north of [[Dimbar]]\n| type=Mountain range\n| description=Unclimbable peaks protecting [[Gondolin]] from the south\n| regions=\n| towns=Eagles\n| inhabitants=\n| created=\n| destroyed=\n| events=The flight of [[Húrin]] and [[Huor]] into Gondolin\n}}\n\nThe '''Crissaegrim''' were a mountain range, forming a part of the southern [[Echoriad]], the ''Encircling Mountains'' of [[Gondolin]], and were inaccessible from the ground.  However they were home to the great [[Eagles]],<ref name=\"Beleriand\">{{S|Beleriand}}</ref> and from here [[Thorondor]], Lord of the Eagles, watched for spies in the vale of the River [[Sirion]].  Indeed, the Eagles were the chief source of information to [[Turgon]] and the [[Gondolindrim]].\n\nIt was from the Crissaegrim that Thorondor espied [[Húrin]] and [[Huor]] when they were lost in [[Dimbar]].  The Lord of the Eagles sent two great birds to carry the men above the Crissaegrim into [[Tumladen]], when King [[Turgon]] of Gondolin welcomed them.<ref>{{CH|1}}, p. 35</ref>\n\n== Etymology ==\n''Crissaegrim'' is a [[Sindarin]] name that includes the root ''kris-''.<ref>{{S|Elements}}</ref> meaning \"Cleft Mountain Peaks\". It is usually referred to as the \"'''Abode of Eagles'''\".<ref name=\"Beleriand\"/>\n\n==Other versions of the legendarium==\nIn early versions of the ''[[Quenta Silmarillion (Lost Road)|Quenta Silmarillion]]'', [[J.R.R. Tolkien|Tolkien]] used the name '''''Gochressiel''''', which he amended to ''Crisaegrim'' (later spelt ''Crissaegrim''). [[Christopher Tolkien]] has noted that the name ''Gochressiel'' might not have referred exclusively to this southern section of the mountains, but rather to the whole of Echoriad.<ref>{{LR|Quenta}}, pp. 285, 290-1</ref>\n\n{{references}}\n\n{{gondolin}}\n\n[[Category:Beleriand]]\n[[Category:Mountain ranges]]\n[[Category:Sindarin locations]]\n\n[[de:Crissaegrim]]\n[[fi:Crissaegrim]]\n[[fr:encyclo/geographie/reliefs/beleriand/crissaegrim]]"}}}